page.title: 17BIRD LIFE IN TAME VALLEY
page.content: The Tame valley is the correct habitat for avariety of birds. There are plenty of trees for resting and long grass where they can mate and hide their eggs. There are many brightly coloured birds such as wagtails and kingfishers.As well as the common birds such as ;crows and black headed gulls there are rare birds.There is abird that has blown in from the coast called the arctic skua.Another rare bird is the butcher bird.It's usually found near railings because they hunt small rodents and stick them on the spikes of barbed wire.They do this to store food for their young. Some of the migrating birds found in the valley are blackcap,willowwarbler and swallow
